race.comment: Keen on the chances of HATCHET (6) on his favourite track. Ran home hard to place in a small field fresh at Eagle Farm but back over the road on favourite circuit and with a great second-up record looks the one to beat. POCKET FULL (7) looks the biggest danger. Fitter for the one trial and goes well here and while fresh. Has the in-form apprentice aboard and with the very attractive weight will be motoring home late. EN POINTE (11) is a talented mare back from a break. Fitter for two trials and while yet to win fresh has a top record this course and distance and will carry no weight after the claim. Has the inside and looks the one to run down. ZOUMETEOR (9) is much better than last couple of starts. Blew it at the start last time and although has a tricky draw here should slide forward and can give a sight. SHOW SOME DECORUM (10) was a close-up sixth on the Gold Coast fresh over 1000m and strips fitter. Extra trip a big plus.
